hopobject.body: i'm fine good work buns of steel workout routine The world’s biggest bird nest was built by a pair of bald eagles (Haliaeetus leucocephalus), and possibly their successors, near St Petersburg, Florida, in the Sixties. It weighed two tons and measured 2.9 metres (9ft 6in) wide and 6 metres (20ft) deep according to Guinness World Records. Eagles make a big sturdy nest to start, then add more twigs, moss and feathers each year until their home becomes huge. Sometimes they get too big for the supporting branch and the whole thing comes crashing down.
